Place "mkcd.sh" file in /bin and give 755 permission(ususal permissions for commands)
Create an alias as follows :
      alias mkdircd=". mkcd.sh"
Understanding the alias mkdircd
If you observe there is a .(dot/period) mentioned before the shell script. That tells us that please execute it in the same shell
as the cd command executes in a sub shell and once the command is executed it comes out to the main shell.
      
Usage : 
  mkdircd test_dir
